cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TY, cs.SE, cs.FL 

This paper deals with annotations in functional programming languages, specifically in the context of intersection types. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses typechecking and typing annotations, which could fall under cs.TY (Type Theory) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also introduces new mechanisms for annotations, which could be relevant to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
